// §7.5 — Each operator lexes as a distinct token. A two-character operator wins
//        over its single-character prefix (`==` over `=`, `<=` over `<`, `&&`,
//        `||`); `/` is division, not a comment, when no second `/` follows.

a = b + c - d * e / f % g
h = i == j != k < l > m <= n >= o
p = q && r || s
t = !u
v = -w
